The paper proposes a model for learning that combines computation and information theories, which is a common theme in machine learning and artificial intelligence research (cs.LG, cs.AI). The model involves optimizing an information function, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the construction of data structures and the extraction of common features, which are topics in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of interpreting the learned knowledge, which is a key aspect of semantic information processing (cs.SI).
